<!-- FAQ -->
<div class="faq">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
      What are the easiest Christian songs to sing at church?
      <span class="faq-chevron">▾</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-a">
      The easiest church songs span only 7–9 semitones and stay in a comfortable mid-range: <strong>Amazing Grace</strong> (D4–D5), <strong>It Is Well with My Soul</strong> (C4–E5), <strong>10,000 Reasons</strong> (C4–D5), and <strong>Doxology</strong> (D4–D5). All are rated Easy on HumMatch and suit virtually every voice type.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
      What vocal range do gospel songs typically require?
      <span class="faq-chevron">▾</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-a">
      Classic gospel songs demand a wide range — often 14–17 semitones. Songs like <strong>Oh Happy Day</strong> (C4–G5) and <strong>Total Praise</strong> (Bb3–G5) sit firmly in soprano/high tenor territory. For lower voices, look for arrangements in different keys or choose standards like <strong>His Eye Is on the Sparrow</strong> and <strong>Victory in Jesus</strong>, which are more forgiving.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
      Are Lauren Daigle songs hard to sing?
      <span class="faq-chevron">▾</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-a">
      Lauren Daigle's songs are rated <strong>Medium</strong> on HumMatch. <em>You Say</em> spans Bb3–F5 (12 semitones) with some emotional runs, while <em>Trust in You</em> is slightly easier at G3–D5 (10 semitones). They're very singable for mezzo-sopranos and altos, but beginners may find the sustained passages challenging.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
      What is the hardest Christian song to sing?
      <span class="faq-chevron">▾</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-a">
      Among the songs here, <strong>O Holy Night</strong> is the most demanding at C4–B5 (19 semitones). Other vocally challenging picks include <strong>Shout to the Lord</strong>, <strong>Graves Into Gardens</strong>, and <strong>Revelation Song</strong> — all requiring 15+ semitones of range and excellent breath control.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
      How do I find which Christian songs match my voice?
      <span class="faq-chevron">▾</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-a">
      Use HumMatch's free vocal range tool — hum or sing a few notes and it maps your range to the songs in our catalog. You'll see instantly which hymns, gospel classics, and contemporary worship songs your voice can handle. No account needed, works on mobile.
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

